subject john paraphras at the end of a recent mon apr post alastair thomson offer the follow paraphras of john god love the world so much that he gave us hi son to die in our place so that we mai have etern life the to die in our place bother me sinc it insert into the vers a doctrin not found in the origin moreov i suspect that the poster intend to affirm not mere substitut but forens or penal substitut i maintain that the scriptur in speak of the aton teach a doctrin of substitut but not on of forens substitut those interest in pursu the matter ar invit to send for my essai on genesi either thru on thi question or through with lead in the n th essai can be obtain by send to listserv asuacad bitnet or to listserv asuvm inr asu edu the messag get gen n ruff your jame kiefer ani theologian worth hi salt can put anyth he want to sai in the form of a commentari on the book of genesi walter kaufman 